Privacy Policy

1. Introduction
Welcome to Vitalio! This Privacy Policy describes how [Company Name] ("Company," "we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you use the Vitalio fitness tracking application ("App"). By using the App, you consent to the collection and use of your data as outlined in this policy.

2. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information:

Personal Information: Name, email address, date of birth, and other account-related details.

Health and Fitness Data: Activity tracking, heart rate, steps, calories burned, and other fitness-related information (collected via HealthKit or similar services, with your consent).

Device Information: IP address, device type, operating system, and App usage data.

Location Data: If you enable location tracking, we may collect GPS data for activity tracking.

3. How We Use Your Information
We use your data for the following purposes:

To provide and improve the App’s features.

To analyze usage patterns and enhance user experience.

To personalize recommendations based on your activity data.

To communicate with you regarding updates, promotions, and customer support.

To ensure security and prevent unauthorized access.

4. Data Sharing and Third Parties
We do not sell your personal data. However, we may share your data with:

Service Providers: Third-party vendors assisting in App functionality (e.g., cloud storage, analytics, and customer support).

Health Integrations: If you opt to sync data with services like HealthKit, we adhere to their data policies.

Legal Requirements: We may disclose data if required by law or to protect our rights.

5. Data Security
We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. However, no system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. Your Rights and Choices
You have the right to:

Access and update your personal data within the App.

Request deletion of your account and associated data.

Withdraw consent for data collection (which may limit certain features).

Adjust privacy settings within the App.

7. Retention of Data
We retain your data as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this policy. If you request account deletion, we will remove your data, subject to any legal obligations.

8. Children’s Privacy
Vitalio is not intended for children under 13. If we learn that we have collected data from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete it.

9. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. If significant changes occur, we will notify you through the App or via email. Continued use of the App after updates constitutes acceptance of the new policy.

10. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us at [Contact Information].

By using Vitalio, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to this Privacy Policy.

